The paper proposes a novel neural network-based framework for the synthesis of impersonated voices. The framework is built upon a generative adversarial network model, which is a popular technique in the field of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also discusses the problem of style transfer for speech signals, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of natural language processing (NLP) and speech recognition (SR). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories for this paper are cs.SD (sound), cs.CL (computation and language), and cs.LG (machine learning). Additionally, since the paper proposes a new neural network-based framework, it could also fall under the sub-categories of cs.AI (artificial intelligence) and cs.CV (computer vision), which are closely related to machine learning and deep learning techniques.
